WEBVTT

00:03.485 --> 00:05.737
Roger? Did you get glasses?

00:05.739 --> 00:07.606
Not glasses, Francine.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.274
Transitions.

00:09.276 --> 00:10.609
[Guitar riff plays]

00:10.611 --> 00:12.210
Best product I've ever owned.

00:12.212 --> 00:14.012
Now, I don't have to switch
out my regular glasses

00:14.014 --> 00:16.148
for sunglasses every time I go outside.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.683
But you didn't wear glasses before.

00:18.685 --> 00:21.620
But <i> now</i> I don't have to switch 'em out!

00:21.622 --> 00:23.756
Ugh! Eyes hurt like a bitch, though.

00:23.758 --> 00:26.558
That dead hobo must've
been blind as a bat.

00:26.560 --> 00:27.626
[Clears throat]

00:27.628 --> 00:29.628
Mama? Papa?

00:29.630 --> 00:31.764
Barry invited me to go with his family

00:31.766 --> 00:33.498
on a trip next month to see the world's

00:33.500 --> 00:35.233
largest chest of drawers.

00:35.235 --> 00:37.169
And I'd very much like to go.

00:37.171 --> 00:38.236
I don't know.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.305
We've never met Barry's parents.

00:40.307 --> 00:43.308
But judging from Barry,
I think it's safe to assume they're...

00:43.310 --> 00:45.778
and this is nothing against Barry,
we love Barry...

00:45.780 --> 00:48.380
monstrously stupid sewer-people.

00:48.382 --> 00:50.248
Agreed. Answer is a hard no.

00:50.250 --> 00:54.052
Another brilliant decision
by my genius parents.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.520
Sass-back.

00:55.522 --> 00:57.656
In my very own home. That's it!

00:57.658 --> 01:00.192
Not only are you not going
on that trip, Smartmouth,

01:00.194 --> 01:01.660
you're grounded for two weeks!

01:01.662 --> 01:03.462
You're so unfair!

01:03.464 --> 01:04.929
You never let me do anything!

01:04.931 --> 01:06.999
- I'm so frustrated, I...
- [Thud]

01:07.001 --> 01:09.868
Ooooh, I feel it coming on!

01:09.870 --> 01:11.670
Don't you do it, young man.

01:11.672 --> 01:13.872
I think I'm gonna go bananas!

01:13.874 --> 01:15.674
- Do not go bananas...
- It's gonna happen!

01:15.676 --> 01:17.942
- You best not go bananas, boy!
- I'm gonna go bananas!

01:17.944 --> 01:19.544
Do it, Steve. Go bananas.

01:19.546 --> 01:21.346
- [Scrapes]
- [Groans]

01:21.348 --> 01:23.682
Aaahgg-blahh-jyaah!

01:23.684 --> 01:26.018
[Screaming indistinctly]

01:26.020 --> 01:27.219
Is this what you want?!

01:27.221 --> 01:29.221
Are you happy now?!

01:29.223 --> 01:32.858
[Screaming]

01:36.296 --> 01:41.766
[Screaming continues]

01:41.768 --> 01:45.037
Is this what you wanted?!
Me goin' bananas!

01:45.039 --> 01:46.905
[Screaming continues]

01:47.679 --> 01:50.042
Sounds like Steve's goin' bananas again.

01:50.044 --> 01:52.310
- [Screaming continues]
- [Thud]

01:52.312 --> 01:53.445
Yep.

01:53.447 --> 01:56.048
♪♪

01:56.050 --> 01:58.316
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:58.318 --> 02:02.387
♪ I got a feelin'
that it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

02:02.389 --> 02:05.590
♪ The sun in the sky has
a smile on his face ♪

02:05.592 --> 02:11.796
♪ And he's shinin'
a salute to the American race ♪

02:11.798 --> 02:15.267
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

02:15.269 --> 02:18.002
- ♪ Good... ♪
- ♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:18.004 --> 02:19.071
Aah!

02:20.207 --> 02:23.408
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:23.410 --> 02:25.610
♪♪

02:25.612 --> 02:28.547
[Sighs] I wish my parents
were more like yours, Barry.

02:28.549 --> 02:29.882
They let you do whatever you want.

02:29.884 --> 02:32.817
I once spent the night
at Claim Jumper's!

02:32.819 --> 02:33.918
That's it!

02:33.920 --> 02:35.087
Claim Jumpers?

02:35.089 --> 02:36.354
Okay, but I think they'll be

02:36.356 --> 02:37.956
on the look-out for me this time.

02:37.958 --> 02:40.893
No, if our parents became friends,

02:40.895 --> 02:43.962
yours are so chill,
maybe they'd rub off on mine.

02:43.964 --> 02:45.830
Then we'd be able to
hang out all the time

02:45.832 --> 02:46.965
and do whatever we want!

02:46.967 --> 02:48.767
It'll be like "The Purge"!

02:48.769 --> 02:50.769
We could go on a rampage!

02:50.771 --> 02:54.173
Together: Rampage! Rampage! Rampage!

02:56.510 --> 02:59.844
Everybody,
the eclipse is about to start!

02:59.846 --> 03:02.180
Everybody,
take a pair of special glasses

03:02.182 --> 03:04.048
from my giant tub of glasses.

03:04.050 --> 03:07.051
[Chuckles] I think these bad boys

03:07.053 --> 03:09.187
will do me just fine,
thank you very much.

03:09.189 --> 03:10.989
Roger, you could really damage your eyes

03:10.991 --> 03:13.191
looking at the eclipse
with just your glasses.

03:13.193 --> 03:15.994
Uh, they're not just glasses,
Klaus, they're...

03:15.996 --> 03:17.596
- Transitions.
- ...a lifestyle.

03:17.598 --> 03:19.664
[Guitar riff plays]

03:19.666 --> 03:21.667
[Gasps] It's starting!

03:24.338 --> 03:27.072
Oooh.

03:27.074 --> 03:30.776
And here comes the sun!

03:31.612 --> 03:34.746
[Sizzling]

03:34.748 --> 03:36.815
Pretty neat... Pretty neat.

03:36.817 --> 03:39.083
Welp, I'm blind.

03:39.085 --> 03:40.619
I do not blame the glasses, though.

03:40.621 --> 03:42.888
Good product. Solid product.

03:46.160 --> 03:48.360
I can't believe Steve talked
us into going to dinner

03:48.362 --> 03:51.429
with that goon Barry and
his cave-troll parents.

03:51.431 --> 03:53.298
Hey, I don't wanna do this, either.

03:53.300 --> 03:55.367
You think chowing down on swamp stew

03:55.369 --> 03:58.904
with a couple of real life ogres
is at the top of my bucket list?

03:58.906 --> 04:00.906
I think when you two
finally actually meet

04:00.908 --> 04:02.945
Barry's parents,
you're really gonna like them.

04:03.043 --> 04:04.142
Nope.

04:04.144 --> 04:06.778
[Doorbell rings]

04:06.780 --> 04:09.647
Stan. Francine.

04:09.649 --> 04:10.949
Outta sight.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.920
Well, get the heck in here, you three.

04:14.922 --> 04:18.055
The fondue's startin' to skin up.

04:18.058 --> 04:22.394
Whoa! This place is incredible!

04:22.396 --> 04:25.330
So much mahogany.

04:25.332 --> 04:26.664
Thick wood.

04:26.666 --> 04:28.066
A man's wood.

04:28.068 --> 04:29.667
Mahalo. Mahalo.

04:29.669 --> 04:31.937
Stan-o, c'mere,
I gotta show you the hi-fi.

04:31.939 --> 04:33.205
Outta sight.

04:33.207 --> 04:36.007
Mom, you know Mrs. Robinson here makes

04:36.009 --> 04:38.276
a mean Harvey Wallbanger...

04:38.278 --> 04:40.011
Oh, it's just vodka
with some orange juice

04:40.013 --> 04:41.813
and a scooch of Galliano.

04:41.815 --> 04:44.482
You put things in your vodka?

04:44.484 --> 04:48.887
Ooh, girl, I feel like
I'm at the Ritz Charleston!

04:48.889 --> 04:50.822
You know, Dad, Mr. Robinson played

04:50.824 --> 04:52.290
a little ball back in college.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.760
- Ted, you played a little ball?
- Yep, little ball.

04:54.762 --> 04:55.961
Little college ball.

04:55.963 --> 04:58.096
I'll be damned, a little ball...

04:58.098 --> 05:00.032
Little ball up at San Jose State.

05:00.034 --> 05:01.433
A little ball.

05:01.435 --> 05:03.035
- Hey, Franny!
- It was just a little ball.

05:03.037 --> 05:04.636
You know Ted here played a little ball?

05:04.638 --> 05:05.837
Ted played a little ball?

05:05.839 --> 05:07.639
Little ball up at San Jose State.

05:07.641 --> 05:10.442
I was actually coached
by John Elway's dad.

05:10.444 --> 05:12.844
[Whistles] Have you ever met John Elway?

05:12.846 --> 05:17.382
- No. But I've always wanted to.
- Me too. Wow.

05:17.384 --> 05:19.184
♪ With the rain in Shambala ♪

05:19.186 --> 05:21.587
♪ Ah, ooh ♪

05:21.589 --> 05:25.257
C'mon, Franny, gimme a bump, sister!

05:25.259 --> 05:28.460
Ooh! Whoop! [Laughs]

05:28.462 --> 05:32.130
♪ Ah, ooh, yeah ♪

05:32.132 --> 05:34.099
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

05:35.469 --> 05:38.670
Bliiiiiind.

05:38.672 --> 05:40.338
Saaaaaaaaaad.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.140
- [Light switch clicks]
- Roger, we are not

05:42.142 --> 05:44.076
going to let you just wallow in...

05:44.078 --> 05:45.543
Wait, why are you in a wheelchair?

05:45.545 --> 05:47.679
I didn't know what kind of
chair I was sitting down in

05:47.681 --> 05:48.947
because I'm blind!

05:48.949 --> 05:51.349
[Sobs]

05:51.351 --> 05:54.085
C'mon, Roger,
you can still live a full life.

05:54.087 --> 05:55.353
Can I, Steve?

05:55.355 --> 05:57.289
I'll never see another Thomas Kinkade,

05:57.291 --> 05:59.557
or a fat guy falling over on a Rascal.

05:59.559 --> 06:01.893
I guess I'll just have to kill myself.

06:01.895 --> 06:03.495
Not on my watch!

06:03.497 --> 06:05.030
We're making it our mission in life

06:05.032 --> 06:08.033
to help you rediscover your
trademark <i> joie de vivre!</i>

06:08.035 --> 06:10.702
We'll see, Francine.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.037
We'll see.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.039
♪ Just an old fashioned love song ♪

06:14.041 --> 06:16.442
Seriously, how do two smokin' hot 10s

06:16.444 --> 06:18.176
like you give birth to this...

06:18.178 --> 06:19.845
and this is nothing against Barry here,

06:19.847 --> 06:22.047
I adore Barry, I mean this in
the kindest way possible...

06:22.049 --> 06:23.715
stomach-turning hobgoblin?

06:23.717 --> 06:26.184
[Laughter]

06:26.186 --> 06:28.386
Ah! You got my number.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.521
Oh, we just like to think of him

06:29.523 --> 06:31.589
as our groovy, little butterball.

06:31.591 --> 06:34.125
Barry,
where've you been hiding these two?

06:34.127 --> 06:35.327
They should hide <i> him!</i>

06:35.329 --> 06:37.729
- [Laughter]
- Whoa!

06:37.731 --> 06:40.332
Cease fire! Cease fire!

06:40.334 --> 06:41.799
Mom, Dad, may I go to the bathroom...

06:41.801 --> 06:43.202
Do whatever you want, we don't care.

06:45.539 --> 06:48.340
[Whistling]

06:50.344 --> 06:52.277
- [Light switch clicks]
- Whup, wrong room.

06:52.279 --> 06:55.347
Never been in this one before...

06:56.950 --> 06:59.685
[Water sloshes]

06:59.687 --> 07:04.089
[Disco music playing on speakers]

07:04.091 --> 07:07.292
"So You Want To Be A Swinger"?

07:07.294 --> 07:10.829
"So You're Currently A Swinger"?

07:10.831 --> 07:14.466
"So You Want To Swing with
Your Son's Friend's Parents"?!

07:15.569 --> 07:17.035
[Gasps]

07:17.037 --> 07:20.572
Barry's parents aren't gonna
rub off on Mom and Dad.

07:20.574 --> 07:22.908
They're gonna rub one
<i>out</i> on Mom and Dad!

07:22.910 --> 07:25.511
That was probably more
disgusting than it needed to be,

07:25.513 --> 07:27.141
but, oh, my God!

07:30.617 --> 07:32.617
Did you know your parents are swingers?

07:32.619 --> 07:34.753
Oh, yeah!
They're always saying stuff like,

07:34.755 --> 07:36.555
"You're money and you
don't even know it,"

07:36.557 --> 07:39.624
or "You're so money."
Or "That's money baby."

07:39.626 --> 07:41.760
Listen, my parents are prudes.

07:41.762 --> 07:43.696
If I don't get them out
of here before yours

07:43.698 --> 07:46.498
come onto them,
they might never let us hang out again.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.367
- Understand?
- No!

07:48.369 --> 07:50.235
- Treehouse time!
- Treehouse time!

07:50.237 --> 07:52.036
Treehouse time?

07:52.038 --> 07:54.573
Have fun, you two!

07:54.575 --> 07:56.641
I spend most nights in the treehouse

07:56.643 --> 07:59.177
while my mom and dad
have wrestling parties.

07:59.179 --> 08:02.314
Time to put on our
blindfolds and headphones!

08:02.316 --> 08:05.751
[Muffled music plays]

08:08.122 --> 08:10.522
Connie: Yoo-hoo! Stan! Francine!

08:10.524 --> 08:13.057
Bananas Foster in the hot tub!

08:13.059 --> 08:14.459
Bananas Foster?

08:14.461 --> 08:15.860
With the bananas shaped like penises

08:15.862 --> 08:17.796
and the ice cream shaped like boobs?

08:17.798 --> 08:18.997
I gotta stop them!

08:18.999 --> 08:21.065
[Grunts]

08:21.067 --> 08:22.534
[Grunts, screams, thuds]

08:23.537 --> 08:26.605
- Stan! Nice suit.
- It's yours.

08:26.607 --> 08:29.141
Yeah, but you really fill it out.

08:29.143 --> 08:31.143
Give it a nice shape.

08:31.145 --> 08:32.876
I need to go to the hospital!

08:32.879 --> 08:34.145
[Dramatic chord strikes]

08:34.148 --> 08:37.282
Ugh, it's always the hospital
with you, Steve!

08:37.284 --> 08:39.417
First when you were born and now again?

08:39.419 --> 08:41.153
Roger: This is stupid. I can't see.

08:41.155 --> 08:42.621
Why are we going to a movie?

08:42.623 --> 08:44.222
Because you're going to experience life

08:44.224 --> 08:45.624
just as you did before.

08:45.626 --> 08:47.159
Okay, but I've literally

08:47.161 --> 08:49.227
never gone to a movie before.

08:49.229 --> 08:51.830
Goonie #1: Sloth?!
You mean the monster that killed Chunk's

08:51.832 --> 08:54.166
entire family after he
went to live with them?

08:54.168 --> 08:56.101
- Now, who said that?
- The other kid.

08:56.103 --> 08:57.169
- Shh!
- Shh!

08:57.171 --> 08:59.504
Goonies never look back!

08:59.506 --> 09:00.639
Was that the catchphrase?

09:00.641 --> 09:02.174
- What'd he say?
- What?

09:02.176 --> 09:04.309
- You're blind, not deaf.
- Huh?

09:04.311 --> 09:06.178
Sorry, I'm listening to a podcast.

09:06.180 --> 09:07.646
- [Cellphone chimes]
- Oh, can you read this for me?

09:07.648 --> 09:10.182
I'm expecting a text
from my friend McDaniel.

09:10.184 --> 09:12.584
- Shh!
- Which character was that?

09:12.586 --> 09:14.519
- That wasn't from the...
- Is it from McDaniel?

09:14.521 --> 09:15.920
I'm fighting with McDaniel right now.

09:15.922 --> 09:18.390
So, if it's from McDaniel,
do not write back.

09:18.392 --> 09:21.059
- It's from Rafi.
- Uch, I'm fighting with Rafi.

09:21.061 --> 09:22.460
He sucks so hard.

09:22.462 --> 09:23.662
Here, I'm gonna dictate
a message to you...

09:23.664 --> 09:25.530
- Shut the hell up!
- Shut up, you dick!

09:25.532 --> 09:27.199
Get outta here, why don'tcha?!

09:27.201 --> 09:30.335
Fine! I told you this was a stupid idea!

09:30.337 --> 09:32.070
- Oh!
- Ah!

09:32.072 --> 09:34.473
That's it!
I don't care if you're blind, bro!

09:34.475 --> 09:36.008
I'ma kick your ass!

09:36.010 --> 09:37.542
Aah! No, no, no, no!

09:37.544 --> 09:39.812
[Crowd gasping]

09:39.814 --> 09:42.747
Did I just... beat that guy up?

09:42.749 --> 09:44.016
Of course!

09:44.018 --> 09:47.019
Losing my eyesight must have
sharpened my other senses!

09:47.021 --> 09:48.220
- Actually...
- Shhh.

09:48.222 --> 09:49.688
Look how happy he is!

09:49.690 --> 09:53.025
Especially my sense of smell. [Sniffs]

09:53.027 --> 09:55.361
You, sir, are a pedophile.

09:57.031 --> 09:59.431
♪♪

09:59.433 --> 10:01.900
[Mumbling] ...swingers...

10:01.902 --> 10:03.101
'Sup?

10:03.103 --> 10:04.703
I... what are you doing in my room?

10:04.705 --> 10:06.438
Just going through your stuff.

10:06.440 --> 10:09.508
Jeez, you look stressed.
What's going on?

10:09.510 --> 10:11.376
Mom and Dad loved Barry's parents,

10:11.378 --> 10:13.245
but it turns out they're swingers.

10:13.247 --> 10:15.113
And now I'm afraid if
Mom and Dad find out,

10:15.115 --> 10:17.315
they won't let me be
friends with Barry anymore.

10:17.317 --> 10:18.650
Don't worry about that.

10:18.652 --> 10:20.519
Worry about Mom and
Dad becoming swingers.

10:20.521 --> 10:22.921
What?! They would never do that.

10:22.923 --> 10:25.990
Oh, yeah? Sounds like Barry's
parents are grooming them.

10:25.992 --> 10:27.392
It's only a matter of time before

10:27.394 --> 10:28.793
they claim their prey. [Chuckles]

10:28.795 --> 10:30.262
Mom and Dad won't know what hit 'em.

10:30.264 --> 10:31.463
And then what?

10:31.465 --> 10:32.731
Divorce. 100%.

10:32.733 --> 10:33.998
They won't be able to handle it.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.267
Mom, sure.

10:35.269 --> 10:36.601
She's the female Wilt Chamberlain.

10:36.603 --> 10:38.336
But, Dad? Not a chance.

10:38.338 --> 10:40.072
No way it doesn't
destroy their marriage.

10:41.146 --> 10:43.275
Oh, hell, yeah, nunchucks!

10:43.277 --> 10:45.878
Michelangelo! Michelangelo!

10:45.880 --> 10:48.947
See ya later, nerd.

10:48.949 --> 10:50.348
[Laughter]

10:50.350 --> 10:52.817
Ugh, sorry about dragging you

10:52.819 --> 10:54.619
to that awful dinner last night.

10:54.621 --> 10:56.221
How 'bout that Connie and Ted?

10:56.223 --> 10:58.623
- What a couple of shitheads, am I right?
- Francine: What?

10:58.625 --> 11:00.959
Connie and Ted are outta sight, man!

11:00.961 --> 11:03.828
Yeah. They actually suggested
hanging out again sometime.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.564
Absolutely not!

11:05.566 --> 11:07.232
Now, you listen to me,

11:07.234 --> 11:09.634
I forbid you from hanging
out with Barry's parents.

11:09.636 --> 11:12.104
Uh, I don't know what's gotten into you,

11:12.106 --> 11:14.573
but how exactly are you gonna stop us?

11:14.575 --> 11:16.308
"Uh," how about this?

11:16.310 --> 11:18.643
If you so much as talk to them again,

11:18.645 --> 11:20.779
I'll take away your Internet privileges.

11:20.781 --> 11:22.314
I <i> pay</i> for the Internet.

11:22.316 --> 11:24.917
Yeah, but only <i> I</i> know how to set it up.

11:24.919 --> 11:27.652
He's got us by the long-hairs, Francine.

11:27.654 --> 11:30.389
Ted suggested we grow out
our pubic hair. It's natural.

11:30.391 --> 11:32.925
I can change the Wi-Fi
password in two minutes,

11:32.927 --> 11:35.393
and it's goodbye, Jake Paul, Dad!

11:35.395 --> 11:36.595
- [Gasps]
- You dick!

11:36.597 --> 11:38.062
What's your problem?!

11:38.064 --> 11:39.664
<i>You're</i> the ones with the problem

11:39.666 --> 11:41.866
because you two are grounded!

11:41.868 --> 11:44.536
- You're so unfair!
- Go to your room!

11:44.538 --> 11:46.471
- We hate you!
- We hate you!

11:46.473 --> 11:49.474
[Footsteps ascending stairs]

11:49.476 --> 11:50.875
[Door slams]

11:50.877 --> 11:52.144
[Music plays in distance]

11:52.146 --> 11:55.280
♪ Jeremiah was a bullfrog ♪

11:55.282 --> 11:58.016
♪ Was a good friend of mine ♪

11:58.018 --> 11:59.818
Roger was so happy when he thought

11:59.820 --> 12:01.820
he beat that guy up in the theater.

12:01.822 --> 12:03.355
This is true.

12:03.357 --> 12:05.290
So, to further boost his spirits

12:05.292 --> 12:07.759
I've recruited his improv team,

12:07.761 --> 12:09.494
Pizza Party Weekend...

12:09.496 --> 12:11.095
Pizza Party Weekend?!

12:11.097 --> 12:12.965
I saw them bomb at the high school gym!

12:12.967 --> 12:15.968
Yes. And today they'll be
working together to make

12:15.970 --> 12:19.704
Roger think he's thwarting
a terrorist train-jacking,

12:19.706 --> 12:22.775
based on my number one
all-time favorite movie...

12:22.777 --> 12:26.445
"Under Siege 2: Dark Territory."

12:26.447 --> 12:28.313
All: Chuckah-chuckah- chuckah-chuckah!

12:28.315 --> 12:30.115
[Train whistle toots]

12:30.117 --> 12:33.304
Listen to that engine sing.
We're really moving now!

12:33.354 --> 12:35.053
